3D Changes Perspectives:: SWAR v0.7.1-rc1-r3 Starter Example

URL: https://example.invalid/private-stream-page
KEY: private-example-value
META DATA: starter, training, public-safe

>>>> WELCOME TO SWAR <<<<

"This file is a quick tour of the most useful *.script features. Open it in Split mode to compare the source with the Reader output."

--- FAST START ---

+ Write ordinary paragraphs normally.
+ Put spoken or teleprompter text inside quotes.
+ Use the arrow-title marks to make clear sections.
+ Use the editor dropdowns instead of memorizing every mark.
+ Open Tools for Find, Spell Check, Linked Scrolling, Teleprompter, Help, and Clean Start.

>>>> READER / EDITOR / SPLIT / STORY <<<<

| Mode | Best use |
| --- | --- |
| Reader | Clean formatted reading output; editing buttons are hidden |
| Editor | Source-only writing and quick edits |
| Split | Source and formatted output together |
| Story | Editing *.arcs records with Arc-specific insert buttons |

"An *.arcs file still renders in Reader and Split modes. The Arc insert buttons only appear while the active tab is in Story mode."

>>>> CLASSIC SCRIPT MARKS <<<<

>> Data or compact cue <<

>>> Verbatim or spoken cue <<<

>>>> Section title <<<<

>>>>> Descriptor <<<<<

>>>>>> Explainer <<<<<<

>>>>>>> Major explainer <<<<<<<

--- A LABELED DIVIDER ---

"Normal quoted speech becomes a readable spoken block."

>>!!
 IMPORTANT blocks are centered and strongly boxed.
 One complete outer quote pair is removed from a line, but a meaningful final quote is preserved"
!! !! !!<<

>>>> MARKDOWN INSIDE SCRIPT <<<<

# Heading 1
## Heading 2
### Heading 3
#### Heading 4
##### Heading 5
###### Heading 6

**Bold**, *italic*, ***bold italic***, ___underlined___, ~~struck~~, and `literal code`.

> A blockquote can hold context.
>> A nested blockquote can hold supporting context.

- [ ] An unchecked task
- [x] A completed task
- [#] A numbered marker
- [$] A money marker
- [%65] A percent item
-# Automatically numbered tab item
-# Another automatically numbered tab item
1. Standard ordered item
2) Alternate ordered item

***

| Feature | Result | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Links | [Copy this address](https://example.com/reference) | Reader copies instead of opening automatically |
| Escapes | `\#` | Keeps a markup-looking mark literal |
| Color | `[#4fd1ff]` | A valid trailing profile colors one object |

>>>> FANCY FENCED BOX <<<<

```text
[Starter Data]
**A labeled fancy box**
Rich *inline* markup works inside the box.
- [x] It can contain task-like lines.
- It keeps the source easy to read.
```

>>>> INLINE ARROWS AND INDENT <<<<

"Move forward ->, return <-, look up ^-^, or look down v-v. Diagonals: ^-> v-> <-v <-^."

-> This source-line starter indents the Reader output by four spaces.

>>>> GOLDEN AND ATTENTION MARKS <<<<

###### Context => This continuation becomes dim-golden <<<<<

###### !This reminder becomes bright golden! <<<<

#########  ATTENTION REQUIRED <<<<<<

>>>> SUPER AND SUBSCRIPT <<<<

"Version #2 and H!!2O keep the visible prefix marks."

"Hidden wrappers: #superscript!! and !!subscript#."

"Cross groups: #upper!!lower# and !!lower#upper!!."

"Slash groups stop at spaces: #12/value returns to normal and !!3/value returns too."

>>>> OPTIONAL OBJECT COLORS <<<<

"This entire spoken object is cyan." [#4fd1ff]

>> A colored cue << (rgba(255, 130, 40, 0.90))

"Show a color token literally instead of activating it: \`! [#4fd1ff]"

