>>>> AFTER THE PAGE BREAK <<<<

>>>> SPLIT-MODE LINKED SCROLLING <<<<

"In Split and Story modes, the Editor is the source of truth for linked movement. SWAR maps visible source-line anchors to exact Reader positions, including tall boxes and seven-line or thirteen-line gap marks."

"Tools → Linked Scrolling makes mouse-wheel and page-key movement act the same whether the pointer is over the Editor or Reader. Hold the right mouse button while scrolling for temporary linked movement when the toggle is off."

"Each pane has its own bottom scroller for independent fine adjustment. Split and Story add one shared bottom scroller that always moves both panes from the Editor baseline."

>>>> TELEPROMPTER <<<<

| Key | Action |
| --- | --- |
| p | Pause or play |
| o | Set 1x speed |
| l / k | Next / previous speed |
| i | Pause 3 seconds |
| u | Pause 5 seconds |
| j | Pause 10 seconds |
| n | Pause 30 seconds |

"The speed slider moves backward on the negative side, stops at zero, and moves forward on the positive side. In Split mode it uses linked scrolling."

>>>> STORY ARCS QUICK LOOK <<<<

"Open examples/story_screenplay_demo.arcs and switch among Reader, Split, and Story. Reader and Split show the screenplay output; Story is the only mode that shows the Arc insertion controls."

>>>> CONVO / MULTI-SPEAKER STORY OUTPUT <<<<

```arcs
Meet Guide||3:2:3||Safe||***>>>> ARRIVAL <<<<\n"A voice calls from the old gate."***||$imported town_gate#||enter; Alice: "We made it."; "Keep your voice down." :Bob; Carol: "I found the sigil."; Dana: "I will watch the gate."; Alice: "Move now."; _The gate opens_; SEARCH GATE -> CLUE FOUND; >>>> SCENE CUE <<<<\n"Normal *.script markup works inside Arc Data."\n>>!!\n"This is an Important story detail."\n!! !! !!<<; ^Ask about the sigil^; *Follow the guide*; [enter/user {unlock}]; @{GATE}; ~brass key~; drop%25||***>>>> ARC COMPLETE <<<<\n"The guide joins the route."***
```

"The first new speaker uses the left talker, the second uses the right talker, and the third uses the centered talker with !! edges on both sides. Additional speakers repeat left, right, center with stable speaker colors."

"Each conversation is enclosed by a top !! CONVO !! rail and a bottom CONVO END rail. Named speech can be written as NAME: \"speech\" or \"speech\" :NAME. Legacy \\User speech\\ and -NPC speech- wrappers still work."

"Normal *.script block marks can be placed in Arc Data with literal \\n separators. Arrow titles, Important boxes, spoken blocks, indentation, inline arrows, colors, and gap marks render through the same Reader pipeline."

>>>> HELP AND SAFE CUSTOMIZATION <<<<

"Tools → Help can load the SWAR, SCRIPT, MARKDOWN, TEXT, and ARCS help files as tabs. Load All opens the complete learning set."

"SWAR.udata and current.emoji are user files. Release patches should preserve them."

